The paper deals with the problem of maintaining information freshness under passive eavesdropping attacks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also considers a wiretap channel model, which is a common topic in networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a randomized stationary transmission policy, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
